\details{
This function implements WCC Method D (stand-level assessment) which is used
when you have tree measurements from a stand but want to calculate carbon at
the stand level rather than for individual trees.

\strong{Method D Workflow:}
\enumerate{
\item Calculate top height (mean height of 100 largest trees/ha by DBH)
\item Calculate stand tariff from top height
\item Calculate mean DBH from all trees
\item Calculate mean merchantable volume using mean DBH and stand tariff
\item Calculate mean stem volume, biomass, and carbon
\item Scale to stand level (multiply by trees per hectare and stand area)
}

\strong{When to use:}
\itemize{
\item You have DBH and height measurements for trees in a stand/plot
\item You want stand-level carbon estimates (not individual tree carbon)
\item You're doing Method D assessment per WCC protocol
}

\strong{When NOT to use:}
\itemize{
\item You want individual tree carbon estimates → Use \code{fc_agc()} or \code{fc_agc_error()}
\item You already have top height and mean DBH measured directly → Use lower-level functions
\item You have all trees measured and want full inventory → Use \code{fc_agc_error()} (Method E)
}

\strong{Note:} If you already have top height and mean DBH measured directly in the field,
you can use the lower-level functions directly: \code{stand_tariff()} → \code{merchtreevol()}
→ \code{treevol()} → \code{woodbiomass()} → \code{crownbiomass()} → \code{biomass2c()}
}
